The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Punters Corner - Champagne for Hall Of Glory
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      Champagne for Hall Of Glory
            STAR RACER                            
	Calcutta: Trainer Vijay Singhs youngster, Hall Of Glory (C. Alford-up), was simply brilliant on his way to winning 1,400m Indian Champagne Stakes on Saturday from the start of the race. The afternoon also witnessed trainer Pesi Shroffs Castle Queen decimating the opposition in the 1,400m Police Commissioners Cup, which was presented by the police chief Gautam Mohan Chakrabarti. The Hyderabad Race Club Cup was lifted by Arti Doctors Raghuvansh.RESULTS          
	1. Flying Glance Handicap 1,400m: (3-4-2) Tokyo Drift (Vinay) 1, Fascinating (Reuben) 2, Bankable (Surjeet) 3. Won by: Hd, 1-1/2; (1-29.33). Win Rs 42; (P) 16, 15, 21; (Q) 90; Shp: 56; (T) 1,065. Fav: Fascinating (4). Winner trained by Vikash.          
	2. H.H. Maharaja Jagaddipendra Narayan Bhup Bahadur Of Cooch Behar Memorial Cup 1,100m: (2-3-6) Cyclades (Babu) 1, Elegant Road (A. Imran) 2, Cosmos (Ruzaan) 3. Won by: 1-1/2, NK; (1-06.3). Win Rs 28; (P) 17, 14; (Q) 25; Shp: 43; (T) 169. Fav: Elegant Road (3). Winner trained by Shafiq.          
	3. Showhouse Cup 1,400m: (3-6-11) Special Star (Kamlesh) 1, Caravaggio (Islam) 2, Accapella (Neeraj) 3. Won by: 3/4, 1; (1-26.67). Win Rs 25; (P) 13, 29, 17; (Q) 266; Shp: 132; (T) 998. Fav: Special Star (3). Winner trained by Arti.          
	4. Police Commissioners Cup 1,400m: (6-4-1) Castle Queen (Ruzaan) 1, Everybody Salsa (Kamlesh) 2, Agility (Mahesh) 3. Won by: 2-3/4, 2-1/4; (1-26.59). Win Rs 37; (P) 15, 14, 15; (Q) 87; Shp: 47; (T) 410. Fav: Duke Of Windsor (2). Winner trained by Shroff.          
	5. Indian Champagne Stakes 1,400m: (3-5-4) Hall Of Glory (C.Alford) 1, Record Breaker (Neeraj) 2, Arbroath (Nirmal) 3. Won by: 1-1/2; Nk, (1-25.77). Win Rs 28; (P) 16, 17; (Q) 25; Shp: 33; (T) 167. Fav: Record Breaker (5). Winner trained by Vijay.          
	6. Hyderabad Race Club Cup 2,000m: (2-1-4) Raghuvansh (Kamlesh) 1, Grand Madame (A.Imran) 2, Silver Fox (C.Alford) 3. Won by: 1-1/2, Shd; (2-5.9). Win Rs 27; (P) 13, 15, 14; (Q) 53; Shp: 43; (T) 204. Fav: Raghuvansh (2). Winner trained by Arti.          
	7. M. B. Medhora Trophy 1,200m: (4-1-10) Snowberry (Kamlesh) 1, Malikah (Imran) 2, Whispering Wind (A.Imran) 3. Won by: 3/4, 1-1/4; (1-14.79). Win Rs 52; (P) 19, 42, 16; (Q) 779; Shp: 167; (T) 3,242. Fav: Whispering Wind (10). Winner trained by Javed.          
	Jackpot: Rs 6,111; (C) Rs 241.          
	Treble: (i) Rs 475; (ii) Rs 410.          
	REUBEN PUNISHED          
	Holding an inquiry into the running and riding of the favourite, Fascinating, the stewards, RCTC, withdrew jockey Mark Reubens riding license for not allowing the horse to run on her merit. Reuben was also fined Rs 25,000 for giving misleading evidence.                                                                                                                                                          
